Hi,
I am using WhatsAPI to sync contacts.
Here is part of my code:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
function onSyncResult($result)
{
    foreach($result->existing as $number)
    {
        echo "$number exists<br />";
    }
    foreach($result->nonExisting as $number)
    {
        echo "$number does not exist<br />";
    }
    die();//to break out of the while(true) loop
}
$wa = new WhatsProt($username, "", "WhatsApp", false);
//bind event handler
$wa->eventManager()->bind('onGetSyncResult', 'onSyncResult');
$wa->connect();
echo '1';
$wa->loginWithPassword($password);
echo '2';
//send dataset to server
$wa->sendSync($numbers);
//wait for response
while(true)
{
    $wa->pollMessage();
}
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
This code run very well from my localhost, evenif I tried it 3 to 4 times.

Now the problem is 
when I tried to run this code on my testing server it does not work.
In first attempt either it does not call 'onSyncResult' after login or gives 500 internal server error.
And in just second attempt it blocks the number, means does not login.

Please give some solution or hint to solve this problem...
Thanks.
